  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWhen one makes the /src/main/proto directory a symlink to another directory, Quarkus cannot find the `.proto` files within that symlinked directory.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nQuarkus compiles the .proto files within the symlink target to java classes within `/build/classes/java/quarkus-generated-sources`\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`/build/classes/java/quarkus-generated-sources` is empty.\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n1. Set up a Quarkus project with the gRPC extension installed.\r\n2. Create a directory with `.proto` files that Quarkus can compile\r\n3. Create a symlink in /src/main/proto that links to the directory in step 2.\r\n4. Run `quarkusBuild`\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\nMicrosoft Windows [Version 10.0.22635.2771]\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\njava version \"21.0.1\" 2023-10-17 LTS\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n3.5.2\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\nGradle 8.4\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
